{
  "doc_id": "30243",
  "text": "While biological containment systems have been implemented in various organisms [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , none have so far been developed for cyanobacteria. Even though induced lysis has been carried out in cyanobacteria for the purpose of recovering biofuel from biomass [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , metabolite extraction does not require complete lysisinduced death, while total killing is necessary for biosafety purposes.",
